WEBVTT

00:00:00.320 --> 00:01:35.400

00:02:40.065 --> 00:02:41.305
Officer He.

00:02:41.385 --> 00:02:43.225
Honey. One mutton rice noodle.

00:02:43.305 --> 00:02:44.505
-Extra coriander.
-Alright.

00:02:45.305 --> 00:02:46.705
To go. Make it fast.

00:02:46.785 --> 00:02:48.505
Officer He. We haven't seen you in ages.

00:02:48.585 --> 00:02:50.625
The criminal department
is busier than the station?

00:02:50.705 --> 00:02:52.425
I'll be back in three days.

00:02:52.505 --> 00:02:55.705
That's good. That's good.
We're all eager to have you back.

00:02:56.585 --> 00:02:59.665
Officer He.
There's a newcomer at the station.

00:02:59.745 --> 00:03:00.985
Officer… Officer Qu.

00:03:01.585 --> 00:03:04.425
We've never seen him smile.
Difficult person.

00:03:05.545 --> 00:03:07.745
Tell everyone to be at ease.

00:03:07.825 --> 00:03:10.905
Once I'm back,
I'll get that poker face out of here.

00:03:11.425 --> 00:03:13.825
Wait. One more noodle. No coriander.

00:03:13.905 --> 00:03:15.905
Alright. One more noodle. No coriander.

00:03:15.985 --> 00:03:17.345
-Alright.
-I'm on it.

00:03:18.345 --> 00:03:19.265
POLICE CODE OF CONDUCT
ON UNIFORM AND APPEARANCE

00:03:19.345 --> 00:03:21.785
I haven't slept for days.

00:03:21.865 --> 00:03:22.705
CONFERENCE ROOM

00:03:22.785 --> 00:03:24.145
Seriously.

00:03:25.825 --> 00:03:27.385
Good to see you, guys.

00:03:28.625 --> 00:03:29.505
Have one.

00:03:30.025 --> 00:03:31.185
I don't smoke. Thanks.

00:03:34.065 --> 00:03:35.305
Hi.

00:03:37.865 --> 00:03:38.825
Writing notes?

00:03:39.505 --> 00:03:41.145
-Let's eat after this.
-Okay.

00:03:46.225 --> 00:03:47.065
Get up.

00:03:49.625 --> 00:03:52.105
Same old rules. Long story short.

00:03:52.945 --> 00:03:54.305
Last night,

00:03:54.385 --> 00:03:57.705
there was a major burglary
at the Dongshan Mine.

00:03:57.785 --> 00:04:00.905
Valuable items
and important materials were lost.

00:04:00.985 --> 00:04:03.305
My higher-ups were on my neck all night.

00:04:03.905 --> 00:04:04.985
From now on,

00:04:05.065 --> 00:04:10.025
whoever doesn't have important tasks
will join the Special Task Force.

00:04:10.105 --> 00:04:12.185
Tan. Give out the materials.

00:04:14.985 --> 00:04:17.624
-Big cases? Ours?
-You in?

00:04:21.145 --> 00:04:22.385
Captain.

00:04:24.265 --> 00:04:26.665
Of course, we should
prioritize the big case.

00:04:27.465 --> 00:04:28.625
Captain Feng.

00:04:31.625 --> 00:04:32.465
Fangxu.

00:04:33.065 --> 00:04:34.705
You already got ideas?

00:04:34.785 --> 00:04:36.265
Tell us about it.

00:04:36.345 --> 00:04:40.505
Everyone here will get to hear
the ideas of a PPSUC graduate.

00:04:48.185 --> 00:04:49.185
Captain Feng.

00:04:49.825 --> 00:04:52.185
The missing persons case
I'm working on is also quite urgent.

00:04:54.545 --> 00:04:56.425
Seriously?

00:04:59.305 --> 00:05:00.585
Seriously?

00:05:02.065 --> 00:05:03.105
Yuanhang.

00:05:04.185 --> 00:05:06.945
Has the case in Yuanlongli been filed?

00:05:07.785 --> 00:05:08.625
Not yet.

00:05:08.705 --> 00:05:10.025
How long have you been on this?

00:05:12.145 --> 00:05:13.225
Four days.

00:05:13.305 --> 00:05:15.585
They've been investigating
around the clock,

00:05:15.665 --> 00:05:19.145
as busy as bees, 24 hours non-stop.

00:05:23.345 --> 00:05:24.745
Yuanhang.

00:05:24.825 --> 00:05:26.985
It's been four days.

00:05:27.065 --> 00:05:29.625
We can't file a case
without finding the person.

00:05:30.305 --> 00:05:32.105
But based on what we know,

00:05:32.185 --> 00:05:34.785
this case is highly likely
to develop into a murder.

00:05:35.385 --> 00:05:38.185
What makes you think
it's going to be a murder?

00:05:38.785 --> 00:05:41.865
Is that based on proof or your intuition?

00:05:45.465 --> 00:05:46.705
Captain Feng.

00:05:47.985 --> 00:05:48.825
On probability.

00:05:50.265 --> 00:05:53.065
Approximately 25% of missing persons cases
are ultimately classified as homicides.

00:05:53.145 --> 00:05:56.585
For every four missing people,
one dies of unnatural causes.

00:05:56.665 --> 00:06:00.585
And now we've passed the golden 72 hours
for finding the missing person.

00:06:00.665 --> 00:06:03.985
Every extra day means more danger
to the missing person.

00:06:08.465 --> 00:06:09.385
That's all.

00:06:21.065 --> 00:06:23.985
Captain, this kid is a bookworm.

00:06:24.065 --> 00:06:25.745
Please don't mind him.

00:06:25.825 --> 00:06:27.505
You think I don't know that?

00:06:27.585 --> 00:06:30.625
I was also annoyingly stubborn
when I was young.

00:06:32.185 --> 00:06:34.345
This kid is persistent.

00:06:34.425 --> 00:06:36.225
He'll make a good officer.

00:06:37.465 --> 00:06:38.945
But then again,

00:06:41.425 --> 00:06:43.905
you are also to blame
for his stubbornness.

00:06:44.545 --> 00:06:46.465
You've been mentoring him for days.

00:06:46.545 --> 00:06:47.905
Is this how you train him?

00:06:47.985 --> 00:06:49.745
How can I mentor a college graduate?

00:06:49.825 --> 00:06:52.225
Besides, you never said
that I'd be his mentor.

00:06:54.465 --> 00:06:58.025
Isn't he sure that it's going
to turn into a murder?

00:06:58.105 --> 00:07:01.625
How about this? Keep an eye on your area.

00:07:01.705 --> 00:07:04.025
Transfer Ran Fangxu
to the Special Task Force.

00:07:04.105 --> 00:07:06.545
Transfer him here to keep defying you?

00:07:06.625 --> 00:07:09.465
Also, we're not allowed
to work cases alone.

00:07:09.545 --> 00:07:10.585
How about this, Captain?

00:07:10.665 --> 00:07:13.585
Give us an official order and a deadline.

00:07:13.665 --> 00:07:15.385
This way, he'll have no complaints. Okay?

00:07:16.665 --> 00:07:18.345
To be honest, I believe

00:07:18.425 --> 00:07:22.625
that a missing person matters more
than some lost items.

00:07:28.305 --> 00:07:30.745
Fine. How many days do you need?

00:07:30.825 --> 00:07:31.745
Three days.

00:07:31.825 --> 00:07:34.465
After three days, I'll bring that kid
to the Special Task Force.

00:07:41.585 --> 00:07:42.745
Captain.

00:07:50.425 --> 00:07:52.145
When are you going back
to the police station?

00:07:55.745 --> 00:07:56.625
Also in three days.

00:07:59.105 --> 00:08:00.705
Sneaky fox.

00:08:02.385 --> 00:08:03.425
I…

00:08:05.265 --> 00:08:07.465
There's nothing in it for me.

00:08:07.545 --> 00:08:08.905
I did it all for you.

00:08:10.585 --> 00:08:13.305
Thank you, Officer He.

00:08:13.385 --> 00:08:15.065
For what?

00:08:15.145 --> 00:08:17.985
You should thank Captain Feng.
He values talent.

00:08:18.065 --> 00:08:21.425
Also, stop addressing me so formally.

00:08:22.625 --> 00:08:24.145
What should I call you?

00:08:26.385 --> 00:08:28.185
Our partnership will end soon.

00:08:28.265 --> 00:08:31.025
I won't take advantage of you
and make you call me "sir".

00:08:32.105 --> 00:08:33.425
Just call me He.

00:08:38.425 --> 00:08:39.904
He.

00:08:39.985 --> 00:08:42.545
I will do my best
to avoid delaying your return.

00:08:48.025 --> 00:08:50.305
To be honest,
I have some selfish intentions.

00:08:50.385 --> 00:08:52.825
This case has almost become a joke.

00:08:52.905 --> 00:08:54.385
I can't go back empty-handed.

00:08:55.225 --> 00:08:58.265
That's enough. Dig in. Dig in.

00:08:58.345 --> 00:08:59.825
Clean it up afterward.

00:09:12.585 --> 00:09:14.105
You like coriander too?

00:09:14.665 --> 00:09:16.105
Have this. I'll have this.

00:09:24.305 --> 00:09:26.265
It's a bit too much.

00:09:46.785 --> 00:09:50.105
The case of Dongshan Mine
is the real deal.

00:09:50.185 --> 00:09:52.785
But you're only interested
in a minor case.

00:10:03.025 --> 00:10:05.185
My parents also went missing.

00:10:06.865 --> 00:10:08.825
At first, they said it was nothing.

00:10:10.585 --> 00:10:12.545
But later, they found…

00:10:28.345 --> 00:10:29.625
their bodies.

00:10:47.345 --> 00:10:49.865
We have three days. We have time.

00:10:56.425 --> 00:10:57.385
Okay.

00:11:12.065 --> 00:11:13.425
Wait.

00:11:13.505 --> 00:11:16.145
MUSE FOOT MASSAGE, OWNER: ZHAO HONGMEI

00:11:18.105 --> 00:11:19.625
MUSE FOOT MASSAGE, OWNER: ZHAO HONGMEI

00:11:20.225 --> 00:11:21.825
How did I forget about her?

00:11:21.905 --> 00:11:27.025
MUSE FOOT MASSAGE

00:11:33.145 --> 00:11:34.185
So annoying.

00:11:43.305 --> 00:11:45.305
Don't slam the door.

00:11:51.425 --> 00:11:54.425
We have zero customers
after the police visited.

00:11:55.105 --> 00:11:56.825
Not even a fly flew in.

00:12:03.225 --> 00:12:04.865
It's all because of Mengmeng.

00:12:05.945 --> 00:12:06.985
Listen.

00:12:07.065 --> 00:12:09.305
No one is allowed
to mention Mengmeng again.

00:12:10.105 --> 00:12:12.785
Do not gossip about her to anyone.

00:12:12.865 --> 00:12:14.305
You hear me?

00:12:17.425 --> 00:12:18.465
You hear me?

00:12:18.545 --> 00:12:20.865
Yeah.

00:12:21.705 --> 00:12:23.825
Lili. Get a perm.

00:12:23.905 --> 00:12:27.145
Look at your hair.
It's like a pot of plants.

00:12:27.225 --> 00:12:28.665
Ms. Zhao.

00:12:28.745 --> 00:12:30.785
I need money for that.

00:12:30.865 --> 00:12:32.265
You haven't paid me this month.

00:12:39.465 --> 00:12:42.705
Why are you staring at me?
Do I have money on my face?

00:12:44.225 --> 00:12:46.265
Still staring? Go get a perm.

00:12:50.305 --> 00:12:54.425
QINGSONG CEMENT CONNECTS YOU AND ME

00:12:55.385 --> 00:12:59.905
MUSE FOOT MASSAGE

00:13:21.265 --> 00:13:22.585
I don't know Mengmeng so well.

00:13:22.665 --> 00:13:24.665
I don't know what exactly happened to her.

00:13:24.745 --> 00:13:25.985
What happened?

00:13:30.265 --> 00:13:33.425
If I remember correctly,
you wanted to say something that night.

00:13:33.505 --> 00:13:34.985
No one picked her.

00:13:35.065 --> 00:13:37.105
She didn't earn anything,
so she stopped coming.

00:13:37.745 --> 00:13:38.585
Why did she miss work?

00:13:39.185 --> 00:13:40.225
I don't know.

00:13:43.905 --> 00:13:46.585
Officer, stop pushing me.

00:13:46.665 --> 00:13:48.505
I… I really don't know.

00:13:48.585 --> 00:13:50.945
I have things to do. Can I leave now?

00:13:51.025 --> 00:13:51.865
No.

00:13:52.905 --> 00:13:54.145
Did Zhao Hongmei threaten you?

00:13:55.265 --> 00:13:57.625
I can arrest her
if she's hiding something.

00:14:02.425 --> 00:14:06.025
Rest assured. The information
you provide will be kept confidential.

00:14:06.105 --> 00:14:08.505
-We're just trying to find Mengmeng.
-Yeah.

00:14:15.985 --> 00:14:20.625
Actually, Mengmeng had some bad luck
right before she disappeared.

00:14:20.705 --> 00:14:21.745
Bad luck?

00:14:24.705 --> 00:14:28.665
Speaking of which,
she took the hit for me.

00:14:34.745 --> 00:14:38.985
MUSE FOOT MASSAGE

00:14:39.065 --> 00:14:40.225
Mr. Song.

00:14:40.825 --> 00:14:42.145
Mr. Song.

00:14:42.705 --> 00:14:44.705
You finally came to inspect our work.

00:14:44.785 --> 00:14:46.225
Be careful.

00:14:48.265 --> 00:14:51.065
Our young ladies have missed you so much.

00:14:52.145 --> 00:14:53.265
Wait.

00:14:54.225 --> 00:14:55.065
Briefcase.

00:14:55.705 --> 00:14:56.785
Hurry.

00:15:00.265 --> 00:15:04.385
MUSE FOOT MASSAGE

00:15:06.425 --> 00:15:10.585
Welcome, Mr. Song.

00:15:10.665 --> 00:15:12.265
-Mei.
-Yes?

00:15:12.345 --> 00:15:14.585
I've traveled everywhere.

00:15:14.665 --> 00:15:16.465
This is the best place for me.

00:15:16.545 --> 00:15:19.425
Wherever you say is nice,
that's the nicest place.

00:15:22.105 --> 00:15:24.505
Don't just stand there.
Hurry up and get around.

00:15:24.585 --> 00:15:26.945
Get closer to Mr. Song.

00:15:29.065 --> 00:15:31.505
Go ahead. Go ahead.

00:15:38.825 --> 00:15:42.225
Mr. Song. Lili. Get him in.

00:15:42.825 --> 00:15:46.185
How dare you snatch my things?

00:15:47.985 --> 00:15:51.305
I'll break your other leg, too.

00:16:00.265 --> 00:16:02.145
Who are you?

00:16:02.225 --> 00:16:04.105
Mr. Song, I'm Lili.

00:16:05.025 --> 00:16:06.185
QINGSONG CEMENT

00:16:07.465 --> 00:16:09.385
Who said you could touch my briefcase?

00:16:09.465 --> 00:16:11.305
The essential oil might drip on it.

00:16:11.385 --> 00:16:12.865
Who said you could touch my briefcase?

00:16:12.945 --> 00:16:13.905
I paid for that.

00:16:13.985 --> 00:16:15.745
Who said you could touch my briefcase?

00:16:15.825 --> 00:16:18.745
How dare you touch my briefcase?

00:16:18.825 --> 00:16:20.185
-How dare you!
-Mr. Song.

00:16:20.265 --> 00:16:21.625
What are you doing? What are you doing?

00:16:21.705 --> 00:16:23.345
Go away. Go away.

00:16:23.425 --> 00:16:25.265
Why are you angry with that dumb girl?

00:16:25.345 --> 00:16:26.945
Don't be mad. I'll get you someone else.

00:16:27.025 --> 00:16:28.465
Mengmeng.

00:16:28.545 --> 00:16:30.345
Mengmeng is very sweet.
She'll make you happy.

00:16:30.425 --> 00:16:32.625
Mengmeng. Hurry.

00:16:34.505 --> 00:16:37.585
Come on. Mr. Song, this is Mengmeng.
Serve him well.

00:16:45.905 --> 00:16:48.745
That briefcase says "Qingsong Cement".

00:16:48.825 --> 00:16:51.145
-So Mr. Song is…
-Song Qingsong.

00:16:51.905 --> 00:16:54.465
There is only one Mr. Song in Weiyang.

00:16:54.545 --> 00:16:57.945
Hundreds of people gathered for a fight
outside the cement factory a few days ago.

00:16:58.025 --> 00:17:00.145
It was because of him
and Cripple Du of the steel factory.

00:17:01.065 --> 00:17:03.745
Those two are known to be enemies.

00:17:05.105 --> 00:17:07.224
SONG QINGSONG

00:17:07.825 --> 00:17:10.585
Song Qingsong met Xu Meng.
What happened next?

00:17:11.224 --> 00:17:14.865
I thought Mr. Song could calm down
after he saw Mengmeng.

00:17:14.944 --> 00:17:16.585
But Mengmeng started screaming in there.

00:17:16.665 --> 00:17:18.785
And Mr. Song hit her even harder.

00:17:20.345 --> 00:17:21.265
Why?

00:17:22.424 --> 00:17:25.464
I think it was still
because of that briefcase.

00:17:25.545 --> 00:17:27.464
-How dare you!
-Mr. Song, spare me.

00:17:27.545 --> 00:17:28.945
Mr. Song, spare me.

00:17:29.025 --> 00:17:30.105
Shut up.

00:17:30.185 --> 00:17:31.625
-Still won't admit it?
-I am sorry.

00:17:31.705 --> 00:17:33.625
Spare me.

00:17:33.705 --> 00:17:36.345
I can make you disappear from Weiyang.

00:17:36.425 --> 00:17:37.545
You hear me?

00:17:38.305 --> 00:17:40.825
I can make you disappear.

00:17:40.905 --> 00:17:41.865
I'm sorry.

00:17:41.945 --> 00:17:43.905
I'm sorry. Spare me.

00:17:43.985 --> 00:17:45.705
-Still crying?
-Spare me.

00:17:45.785 --> 00:17:47.145
Spare me.

00:17:47.225 --> 00:17:48.785
Still crying, huh?

00:17:48.865 --> 00:17:50.185
I can make you disappear!

00:17:52.065 --> 00:17:53.425
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

00:17:53.505 --> 00:17:54.665
Spare me.

00:17:54.745 --> 00:17:56.745
-Still crying?
-Spare me.

00:17:56.825 --> 00:17:59.985
Mr. Song kept beating her in that room.

00:18:00.065 --> 00:18:02.785
Eventually, she went silent.

00:18:03.825 --> 00:18:06.305
Song Qingsong said he'd made
Xu Meng disappear from Weiyang?

00:18:06.385 --> 00:18:07.425
Yeah.

00:18:08.745 --> 00:18:10.465
He kept repeating those words.

00:18:10.545 --> 00:18:12.105
I heard him clearly.

00:18:13.065 --> 00:18:15.105
Any idea what's in that briefcase?

00:18:15.185 --> 00:18:18.705
White papers. A thick stack.

00:18:18.785 --> 00:18:21.025
It hurt so much when he hit me with those.

00:18:22.065 --> 00:18:24.145
Papers? Not money?

00:18:25.385 --> 00:18:26.305
Not money.

00:18:26.385 --> 00:18:28.545
Maybe for rich people,

00:18:29.385 --> 00:18:31.385
paper is money,

00:18:32.545 --> 00:18:35.265
and money sometimes is just paper.

00:18:37.105 --> 00:18:39.185
They say, "Life is as fragile as paper."

00:18:40.945 --> 00:18:42.465
People like us

00:18:44.145 --> 00:18:45.785
are worth less than some papers.

00:18:56.665 --> 00:18:59.425
Did Song Qingsong and Xu Meng
know each other?

00:19:00.145 --> 00:19:02.505
Mengmeng and I used to work in Pattia.

00:19:03.505 --> 00:19:06.745
Mr. Song often came
and asked for Mengmeng.

00:19:07.385 --> 00:19:09.425
He wanted to keep her as his mistress.

00:19:09.505 --> 00:19:10.865
But she turned him down.

00:19:11.985 --> 00:19:14.385
That's why she got beaten
and sent to the hospital.

00:19:15.345 --> 00:19:16.825
Didn't your boss do anything about it?

00:19:16.905 --> 00:19:18.145
She dared not.

00:19:18.225 --> 00:19:21.385
Mr. Song rented her the place.
What could she do?

00:19:24.985 --> 00:19:29.225
The 18th floor of New York Block
is Song Qingsong's property?

00:19:30.665 --> 00:19:32.825
He also owns the dorms downstairs.

00:19:32.905 --> 00:19:35.305
Did Xu Meng tell you
why she turned him down?

00:19:35.385 --> 00:19:37.705
She just didn't want to be a mistress.

00:19:38.985 --> 00:19:40.265
Ms. Zhao said

00:19:41.305 --> 00:19:43.505
that Mengmeng owed a lot of money.

00:19:54.345 --> 00:19:58.025
QINGSONG CEMENT CONNECTS YOU AND ME

00:20:00.025 --> 00:20:01.585
I just got back from a business trip.

00:20:02.425 --> 00:20:03.345
Mr. Liu.

00:20:04.145 --> 00:20:06.705
What I have at hand
is absolutely reliable.

00:20:06.785 --> 00:20:09.425
I'll show you when the time is right.

00:20:10.985 --> 00:20:13.545
But right now, I'm a bit short of funds.

00:20:14.225 --> 00:20:16.585
If you're willing to help,

00:20:16.665 --> 00:20:19.385
you can wait
to make loads of money with me.

00:20:19.465 --> 00:20:20.465
Get back to me.

00:20:25.185 --> 00:20:29.505
MISSING PERSON

00:20:29.585 --> 00:20:32.505
MUSE

00:20:32.585 --> 00:20:34.465
"Disappeared from Weiyang."

00:20:35.145 --> 00:20:37.065
Doesn't that sound familiar?

00:20:38.625 --> 00:20:41.545
You're talking about the guy
in the video rental shop?

00:20:45.145 --> 00:20:46.985
That guy was drunk. It doesn't count.

00:20:47.745 --> 00:20:49.785
Song Qingsong has plenty of women.

00:20:49.865 --> 00:20:52.585
Why would he be so serious
about a massage lady?

00:20:52.665 --> 00:20:55.425
Besides, Wolfie only killed chickens.

00:20:55.505 --> 00:20:58.545
Even if Song Qingsong hired Wolfie,
the murder didn't happen.

00:20:59.145 --> 00:21:00.665
What if he hired someone else?

00:21:01.785 --> 00:21:05.105
Both Xu Meng and Lili were beaten
because they touched his briefcase.

00:21:05.705 --> 00:21:07.985
Why was only Xu Meng threatened?

00:21:09.385 --> 00:21:10.425
And the briefcase.

00:21:10.505 --> 00:21:13.825
Song Qingsong didn't even trust his driver

00:21:13.905 --> 00:21:16.745
and carried it with him
to the massage place.

00:21:17.745 --> 00:21:20.025
What was in that briefcase?

00:21:20.105 --> 00:21:24.785
A business owner usually carries
important documents,

00:21:24.865 --> 00:21:27.065
checks, and bank drafts.

00:21:29.625 --> 00:21:30.545
He.

00:21:31.305 --> 00:21:35.025
Why does it sound like you're trying
to defend Song Qingsong?

00:21:36.185 --> 00:21:37.505
Really?

00:21:37.585 --> 00:21:38.425
Why?

00:21:40.865 --> 00:21:45.185
Song Qingsong and Cripple Du take turns
to be the richest man in Weiyang.

00:21:45.265 --> 00:21:47.625
They pay huge amounts of tax.

00:21:47.705 --> 00:21:49.625
Even the authorities
have to show them some respect.

00:21:49.705 --> 00:21:51.145
You know what I mean?

00:21:51.225 --> 00:21:53.225
What does it have to do with the case?

00:21:53.305 --> 00:21:56.505
We lack proof to tie them to this case.

00:21:56.585 --> 00:21:59.065
That's why we can't act rashly
towards Song Qingsong.

00:22:05.705 --> 00:22:06.705
I see.

00:22:06.785 --> 00:22:07.985
Good.

00:22:08.065 --> 00:22:09.505
You're afraid of Song Qingsong.

00:22:10.825 --> 00:22:12.825
I'm afraid of Song Qingsong?

00:22:12.905 --> 00:22:14.945
I'm a police officer.
Why would I be afraid?

00:22:15.025 --> 00:22:17.825
We fight the bad people
and protect the good.

00:22:17.905 --> 00:22:20.385
We're not sure that Song Qingsong
is a bad guy, right?

00:22:20.465 --> 00:22:23.865
He put a woman in the hospital.
How is he a good guy?

00:22:25.385 --> 00:22:28.105
Song Qingsong is known
to be a sneaky fox in Weiyang.

00:22:28.185 --> 00:22:31.425
We can't just approach him
with Lili's testimony.

00:22:31.505 --> 00:22:33.145
We may alert him.

00:22:33.865 --> 00:22:35.545
We must form a strategy.

00:22:37.625 --> 00:22:38.545
Like what?

00:22:43.505 --> 00:22:47.465
Well… the strategy
is to not scare off the target,

00:22:47.545 --> 00:22:49.705
but also not come away with nothing.

00:22:49.785 --> 00:22:50.865
So…

00:22:55.985 --> 00:22:57.185
So…

00:22:58.985 --> 00:23:00.265
I need to call someone.

00:23:00.345 --> 00:23:02.665
Then I'll tell you more
about the strategy.

00:23:02.745 --> 00:23:03.665
Don't be impulsive.

00:23:07.345 --> 00:23:08.465
What are you doing?

00:23:08.545 --> 00:23:09.745
Didn't you say that we lack proof?

00:23:09.825 --> 00:23:11.505
I'll look for evidence at Yuanlongli now.

00:23:12.505 --> 00:23:15.025
Why do you keep going to Yuanlongli?

00:23:15.745 --> 00:23:16.745
You have a girlfriend there?

00:23:19.025 --> 00:23:21.225
WEIYANG QINGSONG CEMENT FACTORY

00:23:21.945 --> 00:23:22.785
Come here.

00:23:28.305 --> 00:23:29.145
Brother-in-law.

00:23:29.825 --> 00:23:31.025
Come closer.

00:23:37.785 --> 00:23:39.385
I paid you to deal with someone.

00:23:39.465 --> 00:23:41.465
This is how you handled it?

00:23:42.065 --> 00:23:43.185
I can explain, brother-in-law.

00:23:43.865 --> 00:23:44.705
Come here.

00:23:50.065 --> 00:23:52.065
I've told you so many times.
What do you call me in the factory?

00:23:52.145 --> 00:23:54.105
Mr. Song. Mr. Song.

00:23:54.185 --> 00:23:57.665
I made that woman disappear
as you told me to.

00:23:57.745 --> 00:23:59.385
I hired a hitman.

00:23:59.465 --> 00:24:01.145
She and her dad. Both gone.
Only 40,000 yuan.

00:24:01.225 --> 00:24:04.065
I told you to do it in person,
but you subcontracted it.

00:24:05.425 --> 00:24:06.265
For kickbacks?

00:24:06.345 --> 00:24:08.665
No. Absolutely not. I swear.

00:24:08.745 --> 00:24:10.265
I dare not steal a penny from you.

00:24:12.705 --> 00:24:13.865
Look at me.

00:24:13.945 --> 00:24:15.225
Okay.

00:24:15.825 --> 00:24:17.465
Is that woman really dead?

00:24:17.545 --> 00:24:18.705
Yeah.

00:24:19.305 --> 00:24:21.745
I looked into that hitman
before I hired him.

00:24:21.825 --> 00:24:24.985
He's killed several people.
He's professional.

00:24:30.065 --> 00:24:30.945
You saw it happening?

00:24:31.025 --> 00:24:34.505
Yeah. I saw it happening.
Buried in the mountains.

00:24:34.585 --> 00:24:36.105
Buried in the mountains?

00:24:38.465 --> 00:24:39.985
Why don't I believe it?

00:24:40.985 --> 00:24:42.385
Stupid woman.

00:24:43.025 --> 00:24:44.985
Writing to blackmail me?

00:24:50.345 --> 00:24:52.345
Go. Dig up the body.

00:24:54.145 --> 00:24:56.425
If she's really dead, bring me her body.

00:24:56.505 --> 00:24:57.705
Alright. Got it.

00:24:57.785 --> 00:25:01.385
If she is still alive,
you will disappear from Weiyang.

00:25:04.665 --> 00:25:07.025
PUBLIC TELEPHONE

00:25:08.145 --> 00:25:13.825
WEIYANG QINGSONG CEMENT FACTORY

00:25:13.905 --> 00:25:17.065
PUBLIC TELEPHONE

00:25:20.505 --> 00:25:22.225
-Hello.
-What's up?

00:25:22.865 --> 00:25:23.825
Song Qingsong is back?

00:25:23.905 --> 00:25:25.185
Right.

00:25:25.265 --> 00:25:26.505
Did you get the thing?

00:25:26.585 --> 00:25:27.985
I'm not in the mood for this.

00:25:28.065 --> 00:25:29.865
I don't care if you're in the mood.

00:25:29.945 --> 00:25:30.905
Just tell me if you got it.

00:25:30.985 --> 00:25:34.265
Will you shut up?
Are you all trying to drive me crazy?

00:25:34.345 --> 00:25:37.385
Wu Shanlong. We're in the same boat.

00:25:37.465 --> 00:25:40.345
If you don't get the thing,
the boat could flip anytime.

00:25:40.425 --> 00:25:43.225
I got it. Exactly the same.

00:25:43.305 --> 00:25:44.785
It's in the safe in my house now.

00:25:44.865 --> 00:25:46.665
It's safe there. Happy now?

00:25:53.425 --> 00:25:55.425
Ma'am. Any instructions?

00:25:55.505 --> 00:25:58.145
My mom is not feeling well today.
She can't cook.

00:25:58.225 --> 00:26:00.065
Huh? Is she okay?

00:26:00.585 --> 00:26:03.385
Should I take her
to the hospital after work?

00:26:03.465 --> 00:26:05.825
Waiting for you
is like waiting for pigs to fly.

00:26:05.905 --> 00:26:07.265
I'm assigned to a business trip.

00:26:07.345 --> 00:26:09.185
Pick up Xiaohe from my mom's place.

00:26:09.905 --> 00:26:11.105
When will you be back?

00:26:11.185 --> 00:26:14.425
Should I ask my mom
to keep Xiaohe for a few days?

00:26:14.505 --> 00:26:15.665
Last time she was there,

00:26:15.745 --> 00:26:17.625
she chased mice and fell into the pigsty.

00:26:17.705 --> 00:26:18.785
The countryside is not safe.

00:26:18.865 --> 00:26:20.465
And what if there are abductors?

00:26:20.545 --> 00:26:23.425
Well, I'll take Xiaohe to our station.

00:26:23.505 --> 00:26:24.505
That's the safest place.

00:26:24.585 --> 00:26:27.025
Don't let her eat ice cream
and drink Coke when I'm away.

00:26:28.025 --> 00:26:30.585
I wouldn't do that.
I don't even drink Coke myself.

00:26:33.385 --> 00:26:34.345
Fine.

00:26:41.105 --> 00:26:43.465
Countryside. What's wrong with it?

00:26:44.865 --> 00:26:45.705
Get me another Coke.

00:26:45.785 --> 00:26:47.345
Help yourself.

00:27:01.505 --> 00:27:02.585
Kiddo.

00:27:04.025 --> 00:27:05.865
Do you want to go out to work the case?

00:27:07.905 --> 00:27:09.865
I've worked hard

00:27:10.385 --> 00:27:12.905
and made contributions
on the Yuanlongli case.

00:27:12.985 --> 00:27:16.545
I can tell Zhao Jie to hand this case
over to you tomorrow.

00:27:16.625 --> 00:27:17.985
What do you think?

00:27:21.905 --> 00:27:22.825
Tell me.

00:27:22.905 --> 00:27:26.945
How can they put someone
so talented as you on the bench?

00:27:27.025 --> 00:27:27.985
Right?

00:27:28.705 --> 00:27:30.705
Your dad is experienced.

00:27:30.785 --> 00:27:32.225
Plus your Uncle Ran.

00:27:32.305 --> 00:27:34.465
The three of us will join forces

00:27:34.545 --> 00:27:36.625
and crack this case in no time.

00:27:39.105 --> 00:27:42.065
Dad. Let me emphasize it again.

00:27:42.745 --> 00:27:45.265
Stay out of the Yuanlongli case.

00:27:45.345 --> 00:27:47.145
And stop going to Yuanlongli.

00:27:47.225 --> 00:27:48.545
Never again.

00:27:49.585 --> 00:27:51.665
Why are you so worked up?

00:27:53.145 --> 00:27:53.985
Who is it?

00:28:03.385 --> 00:28:04.225
Ran.

00:28:04.825 --> 00:28:07.905
Sir. How's the injury?

00:28:09.065 --> 00:28:11.265
It's minor. Don't worry. Come in.

00:28:11.345 --> 00:28:13.625
Kiddo. Look who's here.

00:28:16.945 --> 00:28:18.865
This kid is so rude.

00:28:18.945 --> 00:28:22.505
Your Uncle Ran is here.
Also, aren't you going to eat?

00:28:25.465 --> 00:28:26.745
Acting up again?

00:28:27.345 --> 00:28:29.865
Maybe work is stressful these days.

00:28:32.025 --> 00:28:34.505
Oh, right. Where were you?

00:28:34.585 --> 00:28:37.105
Why did you vanish when the police came?

00:28:39.185 --> 00:28:43.025
I'm just a teacher.
I shouldn't cause them trouble.

00:28:43.105 --> 00:28:44.905
Why would you say that?

00:28:44.985 --> 00:28:47.825
By order of seniority,
you're their senior.

00:28:50.265 --> 00:28:53.305
Come on. Let's talk in my room.
Come to my room.

00:29:38.705 --> 00:29:40.265
-Sir.
-Yes?

00:29:41.145 --> 00:29:43.945
All these things are about Yuanlongli?

00:29:44.545 --> 00:29:45.585
Yeah.

00:29:46.225 --> 00:29:48.065
These are my treasures.

00:29:49.025 --> 00:29:50.025
And yours.

00:29:56.945 --> 00:30:00.825
NOTEBOOK

00:30:02.225 --> 00:30:03.065
How…

00:30:03.145 --> 00:30:07.305
You walked away without a care
and left them there.

00:30:07.385 --> 00:30:09.785
They naturally became mine.

00:30:11.345 --> 00:30:12.825
Actually,

00:30:13.665 --> 00:30:15.225
I've always had a feeling.

00:30:16.345 --> 00:30:19.425
I've always felt that the missing people
in Yuanlongli in the past few years…

00:30:19.505 --> 00:30:20.185
SONG QINGSONG

00:30:20.265 --> 00:30:23.985
…were related to Xu Meng
and her father's case 18 years ago.

00:30:24.065 --> 00:30:26.345
You saw it today.

00:30:26.425 --> 00:30:29.185
A kid hid in Yuanlongli

00:30:29.265 --> 00:30:31.505
and attacked whoever he saw.

00:30:31.585 --> 00:30:33.785
Isn't it weird?

00:30:33.865 --> 00:30:36.545
Shouldn't we look into Yuanlongli?

00:30:41.985 --> 00:30:45.105
Sir, we found the kid.

00:30:45.185 --> 00:30:47.345
Just leave it to the police.

00:30:47.865 --> 00:30:49.705
We're not qualified to intervene.

00:30:52.385 --> 00:30:54.705
Yeah. We're not qualified.

00:30:55.625 --> 00:30:57.865
You left. I retired.

00:30:58.865 --> 00:31:02.065
But this is Xiaohe's first case,
after all.

00:31:02.825 --> 00:31:04.185
Xiaohe's case?

00:31:04.265 --> 00:31:05.505
Yeah.

00:31:05.585 --> 00:31:07.945
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

00:31:08.625 --> 00:31:10.785
Zhao Jie just announced it this evening.

00:31:16.505 --> 00:31:19.945
Xiaohe is still young.
This is her first case.

00:31:20.025 --> 00:31:22.665
She doesn't catch on
as fast as you did back then.

00:31:22.745 --> 00:31:24.745
This kid is way too stubborn.

00:31:24.825 --> 00:31:28.545
She clearly needs help,
but just doesn't say it.

00:31:29.345 --> 00:31:30.385
Ran.

00:31:30.465 --> 00:31:32.585
I genuinely hope

00:31:32.665 --> 00:31:35.305
that the two of us can join hands again

00:31:35.385 --> 00:31:37.185
to help Xiaohe.

00:31:38.385 --> 00:31:40.505
Rest assured. I promise

00:31:40.585 --> 00:31:45.145
I will do my best
to avoid delaying your return.

00:31:45.745 --> 00:31:46.665
Okay?

00:31:51.225 --> 00:31:52.905
Then it's settled.

00:31:52.985 --> 00:31:55.185
Let me thank you on behalf of Xiaohe.

00:31:59.665 --> 00:32:04.265
YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN

00:32:19.905 --> 00:32:21.185
Officer Ran.

00:32:21.905 --> 00:32:22.865
Why are you here?

00:32:24.945 --> 00:32:25.785
These are for you.

00:32:26.665 --> 00:32:28.745
Why did you buy new ones? No need.

00:32:28.825 --> 00:32:30.785
It's the least I could do.
I have to thank you.

00:32:30.865 --> 00:32:31.865
Here.

00:32:33.585 --> 00:32:35.905
Still, you didn't have
to come all the way here.

00:32:36.705 --> 00:32:38.265
Come in and have some water.

00:32:39.105 --> 00:32:41.585
No need. I have things to do.

00:32:46.865 --> 00:32:49.505
Still that thing upstairs?

00:32:50.105 --> 00:32:52.145
People have been terrified.

00:32:52.745 --> 00:32:53.985
You haven't found her?

00:32:55.545 --> 00:32:56.745
Officer Ran.

00:32:57.345 --> 00:32:58.785
Wang Xinglong said you came
to the fourth floor.

00:32:59.385 --> 00:33:00.785
Wait for me. Be right there.

00:33:00.865 --> 00:33:01.865
Okay.

00:33:07.465 --> 00:33:10.705
Right. How's the injury?

00:33:12.385 --> 00:33:13.865
It's basically healed.

00:33:13.945 --> 00:33:15.105
It won't leave a scar.

00:33:23.985 --> 00:33:26.345
Go ahead. Business first.

00:33:26.425 --> 00:33:28.585
Tell me if you need help.

00:33:29.385 --> 00:33:30.465
Thanks.

00:33:36.545 --> 00:33:37.625
Then…

00:33:50.225 --> 00:33:52.305
CASUAL SNEAKERS

00:34:03.545 --> 00:34:04.425
Officer Ran.

00:34:05.225 --> 00:34:10.744
Do you know the deal
with that woman in 415?

00:34:10.824 --> 00:34:13.225
-What about her?
-She was being kept as a mistress.

00:34:14.264 --> 00:34:15.145
True.

00:34:15.225 --> 00:34:17.985
The one who kept her was an old man.

00:34:18.065 --> 00:34:19.344
In his seventies.

00:34:19.425 --> 00:34:24.625
Last winter, the old man slipped
on the stairs and fell.

00:34:24.705 --> 00:34:26.744
Cerebral hemorrhage. He died.

00:34:26.824 --> 00:34:29.985
That apartment she lives in
belonged to that old man.

00:34:30.585 --> 00:34:35.225
But it seems that he never gave it
to that woman.

00:34:35.304 --> 00:34:39.065
Why did she do that? She's so pretty.

00:34:39.145 --> 00:34:42.665
She could have married any decent guy.

00:34:42.744 --> 00:34:44.784
Why did she pick an old man?

00:34:54.665 --> 00:34:56.625
Officer Ran. We're here.

00:34:59.025 --> 00:35:01.305
After Pattia was seized,

00:35:01.385 --> 00:35:05.345
Mr. Song gave us the keys
to these two floors

00:35:05.425 --> 00:35:07.265
and asked us to look for tenants.

00:35:07.345 --> 00:35:08.785
This half belongs to merchants.

00:35:09.705 --> 00:35:12.625
The left-hand side
used to be Pattia's dorm.

00:35:12.705 --> 00:35:14.025
Which one should we check first?

00:35:15.585 --> 00:35:19.105
QIHUANG CLINIC

00:35:33.825 --> 00:35:35.985
Raid! Raid!

00:35:39.065 --> 00:35:40.665
PRIVATE ROOM 3

00:35:43.385 --> 00:35:44.545
That one.

00:35:44.625 --> 00:35:45.465
Okay.

00:36:09.425 --> 00:36:11.185
ANSWER

00:36:15.385 --> 00:36:16.985
I DON'T BELIEVE DREAMS ARE FALSE
I DON'T BELIEVE DEATH HAS NO RETRIBUTION

00:36:17.065 --> 00:36:18.065
IF THE SEA IS DESTINED TO BURST ITS DIKES

00:36:18.145 --> 00:36:19.465
LET ALL THE BITTER WATERS
POUR INTO MY HEART

00:36:26.225 --> 00:36:27.585
MENGMENG NO.23

00:36:29.865 --> 00:36:31.705
It's their work badge in Pattia.

00:36:39.065 --> 00:36:40.785
This is Mengmeng. Do you know her?

00:36:41.385 --> 00:36:42.945
The missing ghost?

00:36:43.665 --> 00:36:45.545
A suspected missing person.

00:36:48.385 --> 00:36:49.705
I can't tell.

00:36:49.785 --> 00:36:53.265
There are 20 or 30 young ladies
coming and going here,

00:36:53.345 --> 00:36:54.985
all heavily made up.

00:36:55.065 --> 00:36:57.905
I don't recognize her without makeup.

00:37:01.665 --> 00:37:03.425
It's also a dorm next door.

00:37:03.505 --> 00:37:05.945
Someone is still living here?

00:37:08.185 --> 00:37:09.385
Worker of Pattia.

00:37:14.865 --> 00:37:16.745
In the front. Where is she?

00:37:17.345 --> 00:37:18.505
Where did she go?

00:37:36.065 --> 00:37:37.705
Don't throw my cards away.

00:37:37.785 --> 00:37:40.305
Where is the gaming machine? Take it out.

00:37:40.385 --> 00:37:42.425
Do you hear me? I'm counting to three.

00:37:42.505 --> 00:37:44.465
One. Two.

00:37:45.385 --> 00:37:46.385
Hey!

00:37:48.265 --> 00:37:49.545
How come it's you?

00:37:49.625 --> 00:37:51.345
You scared me to death.

00:37:56.825 --> 00:37:59.185
This kid plays games all day.

00:37:59.265 --> 00:38:00.665
He's ruined.

00:38:04.145 --> 00:38:06.065
-Thanks.
-I forbid him to play.

00:38:06.985 --> 00:38:11.145
Well, he hid in the corridor
and kept playing.

00:38:12.185 --> 00:38:13.465
What are you wearing?

00:38:13.545 --> 00:38:14.465
Women's clothes?

00:38:14.545 --> 00:38:16.065
You think I'll go easy on you?

00:38:18.025 --> 00:38:20.385
Ma'am, calm down.

00:38:20.465 --> 00:38:21.625
He's just a kid.

00:38:25.305 --> 00:38:27.785
-Unbelievable.
-Ma'am.

00:38:28.585 --> 00:38:29.945
These…

00:38:32.705 --> 00:38:34.505
Playing games all day long.

00:38:35.625 --> 00:38:37.745
It's summer vacation. So I'm playing.

00:38:37.825 --> 00:38:39.065
-What's the big deal?
-"What's the big deal"?

00:38:40.145 --> 00:38:43.505
Ma'am, I'm here to learn
about the missing person.

00:38:43.585 --> 00:38:46.625
They say this floor
was Pattia's staff dorm before.

00:38:46.705 --> 00:38:50.425
Pattia was seized before I moved here.

00:38:50.505 --> 00:38:54.345
Have you seen anything weird
in the building recently?

00:38:55.665 --> 00:38:58.185
The two next door moved out last month.

00:38:58.265 --> 00:38:59.585
Business was bad.

00:39:00.345 --> 00:39:03.225
The one across, 1703, is a residence.

00:39:03.305 --> 00:39:05.985
We only hear men and women
crying and shouting

00:39:06.065 --> 00:39:07.625
in the middle of the night.

00:39:08.225 --> 00:39:09.425
It's so…

00:39:11.145 --> 00:39:12.225
You know?

00:39:13.585 --> 00:39:15.985
So, 1703 is not a store?

00:39:17.105 --> 00:39:18.705
Officer Ran. I forgot.

00:39:18.785 --> 00:39:21.505
Room 1703 is the biggest.

00:39:21.585 --> 00:39:22.905
Mr. Song keeps it for himself.

00:39:24.825 --> 00:39:29.385
They say Mr. Song
keeps his mistress in 1703.

00:39:29.465 --> 00:39:30.425
Shush!

00:39:33.345 --> 00:39:36.025
Ma'am, have you seen him

00:39:37.065 --> 00:39:38.265
bringing anyone?

00:39:39.305 --> 00:39:42.905
But often, some flashy-dressed women

00:39:42.985 --> 00:39:44.785
come to get clothes altered.

00:39:45.505 --> 00:39:46.945
Guess what.

00:39:47.025 --> 00:39:50.385
The thing is, it's never
the same person twice.

00:39:53.625 --> 00:39:56.185
Ma'am, have you seen this woman?

00:39:57.505 --> 00:39:58.705
How can I remember?

00:39:58.785 --> 00:40:01.025
I do my best to avoid them. What bad luck.

00:40:03.065 --> 00:40:06.665
Don't you want to ask about 1703?

00:40:06.745 --> 00:40:07.785
Mr. Song is home.

00:40:09.305 --> 00:40:10.785
Song Qingsong is home?

00:40:10.865 --> 00:40:12.145
Yeah.

00:40:12.665 --> 00:40:15.945
That door squeaks whenever it opens.

00:40:16.025 --> 00:40:18.185
I would know if he comes out.

00:40:45.545 --> 00:40:47.665
What is this?

00:40:51.665 --> 00:40:52.585
Mr. Song.

00:40:53.625 --> 00:40:56.305
Are you home? I'm the property manager.

00:40:59.865 --> 00:41:01.145
Mr. Song.

00:41:02.665 --> 00:41:03.665
Mr. Song.

00:41:09.425 --> 00:41:10.265
Hello.

00:41:10.345 --> 00:41:11.985
Police, Nanshan Branch.

00:41:12.065 --> 00:41:13.665
I have some questions.

00:41:13.745 --> 00:41:15.665
I know you're home. Please open the door.

00:41:20.025 --> 00:41:21.065
Mr. Song.

00:41:25.465 --> 00:41:26.625
Are you Song Qingsong?

00:41:27.305 --> 00:41:30.465
No. I'm Mr. Song's secretary.

00:41:30.545 --> 00:41:31.825
I came to get some papers.

00:41:31.905 --> 00:41:33.345
What can I do for you?

00:41:36.225 --> 00:41:38.625
-Let me take a look.
-I'm afraid I can't.

00:41:40.065 --> 00:41:41.665
This is not my place.

00:41:41.745 --> 00:41:43.625
I don't have a say here.

00:41:44.625 --> 00:41:45.945
When is he coming back?

00:41:46.025 --> 00:41:49.065
Well… I'm not sure.

00:41:49.145 --> 00:41:52.465
He usually gets drunk at night
and sleeps here.

00:41:57.225 --> 00:41:59.705
Officer, he's in a hurry for these files.

00:41:59.785 --> 00:42:01.985
If you've got nothing else,
please head back.

00:42:04.345 --> 00:42:05.945
It's too hot. Can I have some water?

00:42:06.025 --> 00:42:06.905
The water is out.

00:42:07.825 --> 00:42:10.665
-Coke is fine, too.
-Coke is for me.

00:42:20.225 --> 00:42:21.225
Shit!

00:42:21.305 --> 00:42:22.865
This guy is a burglar.

00:42:22.945 --> 00:42:25.025
Ouch. Ma Qiang. Push.

00:42:25.105 --> 00:42:27.065
This guy is a burglar.

00:42:28.225 --> 00:42:29.665
-Lock the door.
-Okay.

00:42:38.065 --> 00:42:39.065
Go.

00:42:39.145 --> 00:42:42.065
Dad. What's the next move
of the horse stance side strike?

00:42:42.145 --> 00:42:44.185
Kick. Throat lock.

00:42:46.985 --> 00:42:48.545
Teach me again.

00:42:49.385 --> 00:42:52.785
You're biting off more than you can chew.

00:42:55.985 --> 00:42:57.625
GOLDEN ROCK AUDIO SHOP OPENING

00:42:57.705 --> 00:42:59.865
The rock singers all look weird.

00:43:00.465 --> 00:43:02.225
Rocking and rolling.
How can they look good?

00:43:03.305 --> 00:43:05.465
What a heavy bag for a third grader.

00:43:06.305 --> 00:43:10.065
The teachers and parents
are oppressing children.

00:43:10.145 --> 00:43:12.185
Dad. Are we going to Grandma's?

00:43:12.265 --> 00:43:13.585
Do you like Grandma's place, kiddo?

00:43:13.665 --> 00:43:14.705
Yeah, of course.

00:43:14.785 --> 00:43:16.585
She has Hua and Huang.

00:43:16.665 --> 00:43:18.865
We can catch mice in the yard.

00:43:19.385 --> 00:43:20.385
Then let's go to Grandma's.

00:43:22.185 --> 00:43:24.025
-Dad, you're the best.
-Get in.

00:43:29.225 --> 00:43:32.025
Got a lead. Return to the unit. Ran.

00:43:38.185 --> 00:43:41.665
Xiaohe. We won't go to Grandma's yet.

00:43:42.265 --> 00:43:44.505
Dad. You're going back on your word again.

00:43:45.705 --> 00:43:48.745
Want to see where Dad works?

00:43:48.825 --> 00:43:50.065
The police station?

00:43:50.145 --> 00:43:52.345
Are there a lot of bad people
locked up there?

00:43:52.425 --> 00:43:53.345
Are you afraid?

00:43:53.425 --> 00:43:56.145
Not at all. My dad catches bad guys.

00:43:56.945 --> 00:43:57.825
Alright, sit tight.

00:44:07.585 --> 00:44:09.785
Slow down. What's the rush?

00:44:10.345 --> 00:44:11.745
Officer Zhang. Officer Li.

00:44:11.825 --> 00:44:12.745
You clown.

00:44:12.825 --> 00:44:14.385
You're kind of a regular here.

00:44:14.465 --> 00:44:15.465
Can't bear to leave, huh?

00:44:16.425 --> 00:44:18.825
-Thanks. You helped us a lot.
-No problem.

00:44:22.385 --> 00:44:25.065
I'd like to borrow the loot.

00:44:25.985 --> 00:44:26.865
Huh?

00:44:30.665 --> 00:44:33.105
Dad. What did he do?

00:44:34.345 --> 00:44:36.505
Officer He. Long time no see.

00:44:36.585 --> 00:44:38.105
Keep your mouth shut.

00:44:38.185 --> 00:44:39.545
Just saying hi.

00:44:39.625 --> 00:44:40.905
He's a pickpocket.

00:44:40.985 --> 00:44:42.465
I've caught him before.

00:44:43.145 --> 00:44:44.665
Does he really pick pockets?

00:44:46.545 --> 00:44:48.905
Xiaohe. Say hi to Uncle Ran.

00:44:48.985 --> 00:44:49.945
Hello, Xiaohe.

00:44:51.825 --> 00:44:55.185
You're Uncle Ran, the graduate from PPSUC?

00:44:56.225 --> 00:44:57.745
You're pretty well-informed.

00:44:57.825 --> 00:45:01.665
My mom told my dad to learn from you.

00:45:01.745 --> 00:45:03.345
Don't talk nonsense.

00:45:03.425 --> 00:45:04.785
How am I talking nonsense?

00:45:04.865 --> 00:45:07.585
My mom also said
that you should butter up Uncle Ran

00:45:07.665 --> 00:45:09.665
so he can promote you
once he becomes an official.

00:45:09.745 --> 00:45:11.425
Finished your summer break homework?

00:45:14.905 --> 00:45:17.465
Xiaohe. Uncle Ran and I
have things to talk about.

00:45:17.545 --> 00:45:18.905
Go to the office. Finish your homework.

00:45:18.985 --> 00:45:21.145
No. I’m going to play
basketball in the yard.

00:45:21.225 --> 00:45:22.385
Hey you!

00:45:22.465 --> 00:45:25.425
Uncle Ran. Come play when you're done.

00:45:25.505 --> 00:45:26.625
What a kid…

00:45:29.345 --> 00:45:31.065
Right, He. Song Qingsong…

00:45:31.145 --> 00:45:33.345
I've figured out what to do about him.

00:45:33.425 --> 00:45:34.865
Let's wait for him outside
the cement factory.

00:45:34.945 --> 00:45:36.225
-Once he comes out…
-No.

00:45:36.305 --> 00:45:38.025
He will be here soon.

00:45:39.185 --> 00:45:40.105
Huh?